org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions

Interface IEffectDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMetadataDefinition
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EffectDefinition

    public interface IEffectDefinition
extends IMetadataDefinition
    Represents effect metadata decorating a class definition, such as [Effect(name="rollOverEffect", event="rollOver")].

    Use the inherited IDefinition.getBaseName()() method to get the effect's name (e.g., "rollOverEffect").

    Use getEvent()() to get the name of the effect's trigger event (e.g., "rollOver") as a String, and resolveEvent(org.apache.flex.compiler.projects.ICompilerProject)() to resolve it to an event definition.
